						<summary>

						<p>Two broken stones near the cattle pound.</p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI A.D. 1125.</p>						

						<p>This inscription which refers itself to the reign of Tribhuvanamalladēva, ruling from the capital Kalyāṇa, is dated the Chālukya-Vikrama year 49, Krōdhi, Pushya ba [2], corresponding probably to A.D. 1125, December, 28 Monday.</p>						

						<p>It refers to Ghaṭeyaṅkakāra-Chōḷa-Mahārāja.</p>						

						</summary>
